Sentencas: To take the advantage chemical-looping combustion (CLC) process for CO2 sequestration, carbon-air fuel cell (CAFC) and conventional solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) are prepared for high-efficiency series power generation.
Titulo: Conceptual and feasibility study on lab-scale series power generation by carbon-air and conventional solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The tubular CAFC (Cell-I) consisting of Sb anode, (Y2O3)(0.08)(ZrO2)(0.92) (YSZ) electrolyte and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta-Gd0.1Ce0.9O3-delta (LSCF-GDC) cathode has achieved peak power densities of 117, 186 and 295 mW cm(-2) at 700, 750 and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Conceptual and feasibility study on lab-scale series power generation by carbon-air and conventional solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Fueled by repeatedly added 3 g of coconut-derived activated charcoal, Cell-I has operated stably at 800 degrees C for 21 h under the condition of 0.4 A cm(-2) and 0.502 V, with an electrical efficiency of 30.8%.
Titulo: Conceptual and feasibility study on lab-scale series power generation by carbon-air and conventional solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The tubular conventional SOFC (Cell-II) is designed with Ni-YSZ as anode, YSZ electrolyte as electrolyte and (La0.8Sr0.2)(0.95)MnO3-delta-YSZ (LSM-YSZ) as cathode.
Titulo: Conceptual and feasibility study on lab-scale series power generation by carbon-air and conventional solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode exhaust gas of Cell-I, which is operated at temperatures from 750 to 850 degrees C, contains CO and CO2.
Titulo: Conceptual and feasibility study on lab-scale series power generation by carbon-air and conventional solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using this exhaust gas as fuel, Cell-II has demonstrated peak power densities between 87 and 133 mW cm(-2) at 750 degrees C, and performed stably for 6 hat 0.1 A cm(-2) and 0.720 V during which 69.6% of CO in the exhaust gas is consumed.
Titulo: Conceptual and feasibility study on lab-scale series power generation by carbon-air and conventional solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Cell-II has achieved an extra electrical efficiency of 11.0%, giving a total electrical efficiency of 41.8% for the series power generation.
Titulo: Conceptual and feasibility study on lab-scale series power generation by carbon-air and conventional solid oxide fuel cells
